Make the stdio bridge dispatch every JSON-RPC request at most once.

Only the side-effect-free readiness probe is retried while a daemon starts.
After readiness, init, stop, and JSON-RPC expressions run exactly once.
Ambiguous post-dispatch failures produce a correlated structured error with
phase/dispatched/replayed fields instead of replaying a mutation.

